{
  "texts": [
    "Generative adversarial network (GAN) [84] is initially used to generate high-fidelity samples that matched the data distribution.",
    "Some work [14], [168] also employed it as a pretext task for video representation learning.",
    "GANs usually consist of two encoder-decoder architecture networks: a generator producing fake data and a discriminator distinguishing between fake and real data.",
    "However, the inherent randomness of GAN output makes it difficult to control the generated data.",
    "To address this issue, Conditional GANs (CGAN) [83] are proposed for incorporating input conditions such as class labels to regulate the synthetic outputs."
  ]
}